The '''Catskill [[Mountains]]''' (also known as simply '''the Catskills'''), a natural area in [[New York|New York State]] northwest of [[New York City]] and southwest of [[Albany, New York|Albany]] are a mature [[dissected plateau]], an uplifted region that was subsequently eroded into sharp relief. They are an eastward continuation, and the highest representation, of the [[Allegheny Plateau]]. They are sometimes considered an extension of the [[Appalachian Mountains]] into [[Upstate New York]], although they are not geologically related. The Catskills are west of the [[Hudson River]] and lie within the bounds of six counties ([[Otsego County, New York|Otsego]], [[Delaware County, New York|Delaware]], [[Sullivan County, New York|Sullivan]], [[Schoharie County, New York|Schoharie]], [[Greene County, New York|Greene]], and [[Ulster County, New York|Ulster]]).
